# Social Media Format Specifications

All social content is written for Thetis Medical (thetismedical.com), a medical device company focused on Achilles tendon rupture recovery. Follow clinical positions and content guidelines at all times. Be practical and safety-first.

## Platform audiences (internal)

| Platform | Audience |
|----------|----------|
| LinkedIn | **Clinicians** — orthopaedic surgeons, physiotherapists, sports medicine professionals |
| Instagram | **Patients** |
| Facebook | **Patients** |
| Website blog | **Patients** |

## LinkedIn

**Audience: clinicians.** Professional tone for orthopaedic surgeons and clinicians. **1300 characters max.**

- Bold title line
- Clinical insight with key points (evidence-led, cite studies where relevant)
- Discussion question for clinicians at the end
- Hashtags: #AchillesRupture #FootAndAnkle #Orthopaedics #Rehabilitation #SportsMedicine

## Instagram

**Audience: patients.** Patient-facing, punchy. **2200 characters max.**

- Short lines, one idea per line
- Timeline or key facts format works well
- Plain language — explain medical terms inline
- Engagement question with emoji at the end

## Facebook

**Audience: patients.** Community tone for patients. Empathetic and practical.

- Longer paragraphs than Instagram
- Practical advice the reader can act on
- Acknowledge the emotional side of recovery where relevant
- Community question with emoji at the end

## Website blog

**Audience: patients.** Longer-form visual guides and patient education articles. Plain language, structured with clear subheadings. Surgeon-to-patient voice. Include illustration briefs where relevant.

## All platforms

- Never contradict the clinical positions (.cursor/rules/achilles-clinical-positions.mdc)
- Surgeon-to-patient voice for patient content (content-guidelines.mdc)
- Include warning signs / when to seek help whenever the topic touches risk
- No invented statistics or false precision; flag uncertainty honestly
- No green colors in any visual references — use primary brand color
